><H1
><A
NAME="DELIVERQUOTA"
></A
>deliverquota</H1
><DIV
CLASS="REFNAMEDIV"
><A
NAME="AEN10"
></A
><H2
>Name</H2
>deliverquota&nbsp;--&nbsp;deliver to a maildir with a quota</DIV
><DIV
CLASS="REFSYNOPSISDIV"
><A
NAME="AEN13"
></A
><H2
>Synopsis</H2
><P
><B
CLASS="COMMAND"
>deliverquota</B
> [-c] [-w <VAR
CLASS="REPLACEABLE"
>percent</VAR
>] {<VAR
CLASS="REPLACEABLE"
>maildir</VAR
>} {<VAR
CLASS="REPLACEABLE"
>quota</VAR
>}</P
></DIV
><DIV
CLASS="REFSECT1"
><A
NAME="AEN23"
></A
><H2
>DESCRIPTION</H2
><P
><B
CLASS="COMMAND"
>deliverquota</B
> delivers mail to a
<VAR
CLASS="REPLACEABLE"
>maildir</VAR
> taking into account any
software-imposed quota on the maildir.
This manually-enforced quota mechanism is described in the
<A
HREF="maildirquota.html"
TARGET="_top"
><SPAN
CLASS="CITEREFENTRY"
><SPAN
CLASS="REFENTRYTITLE"
>maildirquota</SPAN
>(7)</SPAN
></A
>
and
<A
HREF="maildirmake.html"
TARGET="_top"
><SPAN
CLASS="CITEREFENTRY"
><SPAN
CLASS="REFENTRYTITLE"
>maildirmake</SPAN
>(1)</SPAN
></A
>
manual pages.
Instead of setting up your mail
server to deliver the message directly
to a maildir, configure the mail server to
run the <B
CLASS="COMMAND"
>deliverquota</B
> program in order to deliver the
message,
and specify the
location of the maildir as the argument to
<B
CLASS="COMMAND"
>deliverquota</B
>.</P
><P
>The second argument to <B
CLASS="COMMAND"
>deliverquota</B
> is optional.
If present, <VAR
CLASS="REPLACEABLE"
>quota</VAR
> specifies a new quota setting
for this maildir.
Specifying <VAR
CLASS="REPLACEABLE"
>quota</VAR
> is equivalent to running
<A
HREF="maildirmake.html"
TARGET="_top"
><SPAN
CLASS="CITEREFENTRY"
><SPAN
CLASS="REFENTRYTITLE"
>maildirmake</SPAN
>(1)</SPAN
></A
>
with the <VAR
CLASS="OPTION"
>-q</VAR
> option.
The second argument to <B
CLASS="COMMAND"
>deliverquota</B
> is considered obsolete,
and may be removed in the future.</P
><P
><B
CLASS="COMMAND"
>deliverquota</B
> reads the message from standard input
and delivers it
to <VAR
CLASS="REPLACEABLE"
>maildir</VAR
>.
<VAR
CLASS="REPLACEABLE"
>maildir</VAR
>
may specify a path directly to a maildir folder,
not the main <VAR
CLASS="REPLACEABLE"
>maildir</VAR
>
(as long as the folder was created by the
<A
HREF="maildirmake.html"
TARGET="_top"
><SPAN
CLASS="CITEREFENTRY"
><SPAN
CLASS="REFENTRYTITLE"
>maildirmake</SPAN
>(1)</SPAN
></A
> command.</P
><P
>The <VAR
CLASS="OPTION"
>-c</VAR
> option automatically creates the maildir,
and all missing parent subdirectories (as '<B
CLASS="COMMAND"
>mkdir -p</B
>').
This option should be used with caution.</P
><P
>The <VAR
CLASS="OPTION"
>-w N</VAR
> option places a warning message
into the maildir if the maildir has a quota setting, and after
the message was successfully delivered the maildir was at least
<VAR
CLASS="REPLACEABLE"
>N</VAR
> percent full.
The warning message is copied verbatim from
<TT
CLASS="FILENAME"
>@sysconfdir@/quotawarnmsg</TT
> with the addition of the
"<TT
CLASS="LITERAL"
>Date:</TT
>" and
"<TT
CLASS="LITERAL"
>Message-Id:</TT
>" headers.
The warning is repeated every 24 hours (at least), until the maildir drops
below
<VAR
CLASS="REPLACEABLE"
>N</VAR
> percent full.</P
></DIV
><DIV
CLASS="REFSECT1"
><A
NAME="AEN67"
></A
><H2
>RETURN CODE</H2
><P
><B
CLASS="COMMAND"
>deliverquota</B
> delivers the message to the maildir
and terminates with
exit code 0 if the message can be delivered without going over quota.</P
><P
>If the maildir is over its specified quota, <B
CLASS="COMMAND"
>deliverquota</B
>
terminates with exit code 77 (EX_NOPERM).</P
></DIV
